description.narrative: Emergency response for epidemics, cyclones and drought in the south was an entry point to strengthen the health system and community health functions. UNICEF supported prepositioning of emergency stock in all sites at central as well at regional level covering 300,000 beneficiaries. A national preparedness and multi-risk contingency plan including plague and measles response was completed with UNICEF support. During the measles outbreak, UNICEF played a key role in coordination, planning, vaccine procurement and campaign implementation and helped stop the outbreak | Status:On-track | As-of Date:31/12/2019
